race.comment: THE DEPUTY (5) missed a lip here twice at this level before being backed off the map in Open grade at Rockhampton placing second behind a dominant winner. That was better than it appeared, and with the 2kg claim he finds the right race. FAKE MAGIC (3) has been briefly freshened and he's switched back to the Gorman yard. He was only beaten 1.5L in a Gold Coast Open last time, and her two runs prior also read well. Has the inside barrier and winning claims. GIDDAY GIDDAY (11)was plain at the Gold Coast but was on speed beaten a nose here prior. Maps well and keeps the handy 2kg claim. On a 7-day return, and can bounce without surprise. THE LOUVRE (7) has to manage an awkward barrier, but he's also going well enough to consider.
